===Noun===
#(historical) June 6th, 1944, the [[date]] during [[World War II]] when the [[allies]] [[invade]]d western Europe.  This took place on the beaches of Normandy.  Suprisingly, Erwin Rommel, who was in charge of the beaches, went home '''this one day''' for his anniversary.  He normally never left his post.  The Germans could have possibly won if he was there to command the troops.  The invasion force consisted of Americans, British, and even Canadians.  This was the first battle, on a long string of battles, that had to happen, in order to have peace and tranquility for Europe.
#(figuratively) The date of any major [[event]] planned for the [[future]].
